Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery oinochoe; exterior: glazed black (fired streaky brown); inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 100 (= Well 2)
Curator's comments: Almost certainly from same jug as 1886,0401.488. Well 2 written in pencil.

Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 662, no. 193)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.428)
